<br>
Then there's the newbie aspect. How on earth are they supposed to know you're launching a bolt that requires LoS without the trial and error of seeing the bolt hit the target. How do they learn not to have a tank in the way? How do they learn they are breaking mez cos the mezzed mob was in the way? How do they learn to fire uphill? This is a MAJOR part of a mage's developement that is being denied.<br>
<br>
And finally, and arguably equally important, bolt graphics are part of the game, just like player graphics, just like NPC graphics, just like world graphics. Without them, we might as well just go back to text based MUDs. But why don't we? Cos the graphics are an important part of the EQ gaming experience, take them away and you're cheapening the whole experience. And before anyone starts ranting about no one using the generic spell effects as a counter argument, with the recent changes, and a good PC, they become very viable and I use them all the time. With a low density and opacity, you can have the visual pleasure of spell effects with little effect to gameplay (not seeing what you're able to do, horrible frame rates), even on raids.<br>
<br>
Bring back the Bolt Graphic!!! <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=38898">Salash Penumbra</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> - <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower">Summoner</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> of <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.midnightfury.org">Armies</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->!</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=thedwellerindarkness@themagicianstower>thedwellerindarkness</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 433<br> <font color=#333333>(1/28/03 4:14:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8606.topic&index=26>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Bolts</span><hr size=1> &quot;Heh. That'd be a harsh lesson for melee on PvP. Do not stand between your target and your heavy artillary (mage)&quot;<br>
